// =============================================================================
// core/security/aead/mod.vr — Authenticated Encryption with Associated Data
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Security / AEAD
// =============================================================================
//
// Authenticated Encryption with Associated Data (AEAD) primitives.
// AEAD provides confidentiality + integrity + authenticity in a
// single primitive — the standard recommendation for modern
// symmetric encryption (NIST SP 800-38D, RFC 7539, RFC 8439).
//
//   * `aes_gcm.vr`         — AES-128-GCM / AES-256-GCM (NIST SP
//                            800-38D, RFC 5288). Default choice for
//                            interop with hardware AES-NI / ARMv8
//                            crypto extensions.
//   * `chacha20_poly1305.vr` — ChaCha20-Poly1305 (RFC 7539 / 8439).
//                              Constant-time on every CPU; preferred
//                              when AES-NI is unavailable or
//                              side-channel resistance is paramount.
//
// Both ciphers expose the same `aead_encrypt` / `aead_decrypt`
// surface so callers can swap algorithms via configuration without
// code changes. Failed decryption surfaces as `AeadError.AuthFailed`
// — never silent on tag mismatch.
// =============================================================================

module core.security.aead;

public module aes_gcm;
public module chacha20_poly1305;
